>[Question]
>My question states that:
>"The frequency ratio corresponding to an equal-tempered semitone is 
>r=2^1/12.  Find a quick way to see that r is irrational."
>
>[Difficulty]
>I've tried to approach this question like the proof that the square 
>root of 2 is irrational... I'm just not sure if i'm on the right 
>track...
>
>[Thoughts]
>I've started by assuming that 2^1/12 is rational and am trying to 
>prove by contradiction that it is in fact not rational...
>
>I've said that 2^1/12 = a/b , where a,b, are whole numbers and at 
>least one of which is odd...
>
>~ a^12 = 2b^12
>~ then a^12 is a multiple of 2
>~ so a must be a multiple of 2
>~ then i've let a=2c , where c is some whole number
>~ so (2^12)(c^12)=2b^12
>~ then b^12= (2^11)(c^12)
>~ this shows that b^12 is a multiple of 2
>~ then b must be a multiple of 2
>
>~ so we've proved by contradiction that 2^1/12 is an irrational 
>number....
>
>I just don't know if this is actually correct or not... or if there 
>is a simpler or more direct method of answering this question...
>I really need feedback and help!!
>
>Thanks a lot!!

